# Zig build artifacts. jac/.gitignore covers the in-tree binary build under jac/,
# but `jac run` invoking the native backend emits a .zig-cache/ at the *repo
# root* (its cwd) too -- and a release `git add -A` (release.yml) will
# otherwise sweep in the >100 MB outputs and get rejected by GitHub's file-size
# limit. These patterns are path-anchored to any depth, so they catch both.
.zig-cache/
zig-out/

# Agent / IDE working notes (not repo artifacts)
AGENTS.md
PLAN.md
IMPLEMENTATION.md
RUNTIME_SPLIT_PROGRESS.md

# Claude Code local instructions
CLAUDE.local.md
.claude/

jactastic/**
.mcp.json
.gstack/

# Docs "Build Anything" track pages live under docs/docs/build/ — the bare
# `build` rule above would otherwise ignore them. Keep this content tracked.
!docs/docs/build/
!docs/docs/build/**

# Zig 0.16 project-local package cache (fetched, hash-pinned deps)
zig-pkg/
